Engin, Larson &amp; Erhan, 2018
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F74FFE3FD14FA01FCABFA40" box="[757,843,1415,1441]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="34.[151,250,2006,2030]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,1147,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-44@34.[167,1421,1147,1983]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 35. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Hazeus ingressus. Photo by S. Engin, Fethiye, Turkey, Levant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601679/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
)—Invaded Sand Goby
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F74FFE3FF76FA4BFD0EF9CD" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF76FA4BFBABFA05" blockId="65.[151,1099,1484,1508]" box="[151,1099,1484,1508]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="C9DF11F33F74FFE3FF76FA4BFBABFA05" box="[151,1099,1484,1508]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<treatmentCitation id="686E10CC3F74FFE3FF76FA4BFD4FFA05" author="Engin, S. &amp; Larson, H. K. &amp; Irmak, E." box="[151,687,1484,1508]" page="318" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" year="2018">
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F74FFE3FF76FA4BFD4FFA05" authority="Engin, Larson &amp; Irmak, 2018: 318" authorityName="Engin, Larson &amp; Irmak" authorityPageNumber="318" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,687,1484,1508]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Hazeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ingressus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FF76FA4BFEA7FA05" box="[151,327,1485,1508]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Hazeus ingressus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F74FFE3FEACFA4AFD4FFA05" author="Engin, S. &amp; Larson, H. K. &amp; Irmak, E." box="[333,687,1484,1508]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="316 - 325" refId="ref54201" refString="Engin, S., Larson, H. K. &amp; Irmak, E. (2018 b) Hazeus ingressus sp. nov. a new goby species (Perciformes: Gobiidae) and a new invasion in the Mediterranean Sea. Mediterranean Marine Science, 19, 316 - 325. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 14336" type="journal article" year="2018">Engin, Larson &amp; Irmak, 2018: 318</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
; eastern mediterranean, 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F74FFE3FC44FA4AFC0EFA05" box="[933,1006,1484,1508]" name="Turkey" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, Fethiye.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF76F994FD0EF9CD" blockId="65.[151,1437,1554,2013]" box="[151,750,1554,1581]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Size. Largest specimen examined 
<quantity id="2E379B383F74FFE3FDF5F995FD80F9CC" box="[532,608,1555,1581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="cm" value="3.7">3.7 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F74FFE0FF26F9B0FC7CFF34" lastPageId="66" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26F9B0FAB6F900" blockId="65.[151,1437,1554,2013]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Morphology. D VI + I,8; A I,8–9; P 17–18. Body moderately elongate, the depth 5.0– 
<quantity id="2E379B383F74FFE3FB7FF9B0FB3FF9B1" box="[1182,1247,1590,1617]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6001999999999998" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="in" value="6.3">6.3 in</quantity>
standard length. Stout head with slightly rounded snout and large eyes extending slightly above dorsal profile. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FE28F9F8FD22F95C" bold="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">First spine of first and second dorsal fins stout and sharp-tipped; third spine of the first dorsal fin slightly longest but not elongate</emphasis>
. Caudal fin rounded, shorter than head length. Body, nape, cheek and opercle scaled, but scales not visible or poorly visible on live specimen photographs (Engin 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FB2FF941FAE0F901" box="[1230,1280,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">et al</emphasis>
. 2018).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26F96CFD08F890" blockId="65.[151,1437,1554,2013]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FE60F96DFD18F8C9" bold="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Pale gray with numerous small irregular brown spots on body and dorsally on head, and a row of 5 irregular blackish blotches along midside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F74FFE3FCE6F888FCB9F8C8" box="[775,857,1806,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="34.[151,250,2006,2030]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,1147,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-44@34.[167,1421,1147,1983]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 35. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Hazeus ingressus. Photo by S. Engin, Fethiye, Turkey, Levant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601679/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
), first below first dorsal fin, fifth on caudal-fin base. Head with brown marking below orbit. Second dorsal fin with brown streaks along rays. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FB90F8B5FD89F891" bold="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">No rows of elongate spots on cheek and no longitudinal eye stripe</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F74FFE3FD98F8D0FD3CF890" box="[633,732,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 33. The mouth unmarked at corner in A) G. bucchichi and B) H. ingressus. Dark dot on the corner of the mouth in C) G. auratus, D) G. incognitus, E) G. xanthocephalus and F) G. fallax. Area marked with hollow circle. Photos by R. Svensen (A), S. Engin (B), M. Kovačić (C, D, F), and P. Louisy (E). C and F photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601673/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Fig. 33b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26F8FCFD10F874" blockId="65.[151,1437,1554,2013]" box="[199,752,1914,1941]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F74FFE3FE9EF8FCFDACF875" authorityName="Kovacic &amp; Sanda, 2016:" authorityYear="1106" box="[383,588,1914,1940]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="incognitus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FE9EF8FCFDACF875" box="[383,588,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Gobius incognitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F74FFE3FDBBF8FDFD09F875" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1870" box="[602,745,1914,1941]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bucchichi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FDBBF8FDFD8EF874" box="[602,622,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FD9DF8FCFD09F875" box="[636,745,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">bucchichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26F818FAC0F858" blockId="65.[151,1437,1554,2013]" box="[199,1312,1950,1977]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Habitat. Inhabits sand bottom in sheltered bays and lagoons at depth of 
<quantity id="2E379B383F74FFE3FC08F818FBDEF858" box="[1001,1086,1950,1977]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="m" value="21.0" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="5.0">5–37 m</quantity>
(Engin 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FB79F819FB30F859" box="[1176,1232,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">et al.</emphasis>
2018).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26F844FA7CF83D" blockId="65.[151,1437,1554,2013]" box="[199,1436,1986,2013]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Geographic distribution. Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="3674887F3F74FFE3FD00F845FCF1F83C" box="[737,785,1987,2013]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
specimens collected at Fethiye on the Levantine coast of
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF76FF11FC7CFF34" blockId="66.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F77FFE0FF76FF11FF08FF50" box="[151,232,151,177]" name="Turkey" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, eastern Mediterranean Sea. It was later observed in Abu Dabab lagoon, Marsa Alam, 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F77FFE0FB20FF11FAE4FF50" box="[1217,1284,151,177]" name="Egypt" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Egypt</collectingCountry>
on silty sand bottom (based on an unpublished photograph provided by B. Hazes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
